main event: Two different observers watched an egg-shaped fiery object pass overhead at a high rate of speed in Yorktown-Walden, New York on February 5, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared to have exhaust or flame coming from the rear.
The object was traveling at a high rate of speed and disappeared from both witnesses' sight.

An F-101 aircraft was traveling a low-level pass over the runway at Stewart AFB at approximately the same time, and the pilot lit the afterburner and turned right, which the observers believe was the object they saw.
The object was described as egg-shaped, white and pink in color, and making a thunderous noise as it passed over the observers' house.
Both observers stated that the object shook the house as it passed overhead.
result: likely explained as an F-101 aircraft
